<Docs title="Presenter (MVP)" description="State → view, nothing more." eyebrow="Pattern">
  <p><strong>Where:</strong> <code>src/presenters/</code>.</p>
  <p>
    <strong>The rule:</strong> observe state, translate into view calls, expose a narrow API
    for the FSM to drive. Never decide timing. Never mutate state.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>MVP vs MVVM:</strong> close cousins. slotplate uses presenters because they tend
    to be thinner than ViewModels — no two-way binding, just observable read and view write.
  </p>
</Docs>
